eu.fbk.knowledgestore

Class Outcome

  • java.lang.Object
    • eu.fbk.knowledgestore.Outcome
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable, Comparable<Outcome>

    public final class Outcome
extends Object
implements Comparable<Outcome>, Serializable
    The outcome of the invocation of a KnowledgeStore operation.

    An Outcome instance encodes the outcome of an Operation invocation. It stores:

    • the Outcome.Status code specifying whether and how the invocation was successful or failed (see getStatus());
    • the invocation ID, which is generated by the system and may link to additional information logged on client/server sides (see getInvocationID());
    • an optional object ID, in case the invocation was applied to a specific object (see getObjectID());
    • an optional message, providing additional information about the outcome (see getMessage())

    Outcome instances can be created using one of the static factory methods create(Status, URI), create(Status, URI, URI), create(Status, URI, URI, String). Equality and comparison are performed based on the invocation ID. This class is immutable and thus thread safe.

      • decode

        public static Stream<Outcome> decode(Stream<org.openrdf.model.Statement> stream,
                                     @Nullable
                                     Boolean chunked)
        Performs RDF-to-outcome decoding by converting a stream of RDF statements in a stream of outcomes. Parameter chunked specifies whether the input statement stream is chunked, i.e., organized as a sequence of statement chunks with each chunk containing the statements for an outcome. Chunked RDF streams noticeably speed up decoding, and are always produced by the KnowledgeStore API. Chunking information may be set to null (e.g., because unknown at the time the method is called): in this case, it will be read from metadata attribute "chunked" attached to the stream; reading will happen just before decoding will take place, i.e., when a terminal stream operation will be called.
        Parameters:
        stream - the stream of statements to decode
        chunked - true if the input statement stream is chunked, null if to be read from stream metadata
        Returns:
        the resulting stream of outcomes
